content.text:
Full picture. Here's the complete audit:

---

## Requirement 1 — React & Vite Bundle Optimization

### Already implemented ✓
- `@vitejs/plugin-react-swc` — SWC compiler (faster than Babel)
- All heavy pages use `React.lazy` + `Suspense` with `PageLoader` fallback
- PWA with Workbox runtime caching for Supabase requests

### Missing ✗
- No `manualChunks` — all vendor code ships as one massive chunk
- No `build.rollupOptions` at all
- Paystack script loaded **synchronously in `<head>`** — blocks page render on every visit even for users who never pay

**What to add to `vite.config.ts`:**
```ts
build: {
  rollupOptions: {
    output: {
      manualChunks: {
        'vendor-react':    ['react', 'react-dom', 'react-router-dom'],
        'vendor-supabase': ['@supabase/supabase-js'],
        'vendor-ui':       ['@radix-ui/react-dialog', '@radix-ui/react-dropdown-menu',
                            '@radix-ui/react-select', '@radix-ui/react-tabs'],
        'vendor-query':    ['@tanstack/react-query'],
        'vendor-charts':   ['recharts'],
        'vendor-date':     ['date-fns'],
      },
    },
  },
  chunkSizeWarningLimit: 500,
},
```

**Why this matters:** Without `manualChunks`, Vite bundles React, Supabase, Recharts, and Radix UI into a single `vendor` chunk. With it, the browser can cache each vendor chunk independently — when you ship a UI update, users only re-download the UI chunk, not React or Supabase again.

---

## Requirement 2 — Database Indexes

### Already implemented ✓
- `idx_kira_conversations_user_id`
- `idx_kira_messages_conversation_id`
- `kira_memories_embedding_idx` (vector/IVFFlat)
- `idx_notifications_user_id`
- `idx_notifications_user_unread`

### Missing ✗ — These tables have zero indexes on hot columns:

```sql
-- invoices
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_invoices_user_id       ON public.invoices(user_id);
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_invoices_status        ON public.invoices(status);

-- canvases
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_canvases_user_id       ON public.canvases(user_id);

-- saved_clients
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_saved_clients_user_id  ON public.saved_clients(user_id);

-- chat rooms & members (workspace queries)
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_chat_room_members_user_id ON public.chat_room_members(user_id);
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_chat_room_members_room_id ON public.chat_room_members(room_id);
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_chat_messages_room_id     ON public.chat_messages(room_id);
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_chat_messages_created_at  ON public.chat_messages(created_at DESC);

-- profiles (public profile lookup by handle)
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_profiles_handle        ON public.profiles(handle);

-- kira memories (user-scoped lookups alongside vector search)
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_kira_memories_user_id  ON public.kira_memories(user_id);
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_kira_memories_created  ON public.kira_memories(created_at DESC);

-- payment transactions
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_payment_transactions_user_id ON public.payment_transactions(user_id);

-- workspace invites (token lookup on accept)
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_workspace_invites_token ON public.workspace_invites(token);
```

**Impact:** Every query that filters by `user_id` currently does a full table scan. At 10,000 rows, that's fine. At 100,000 rows it becomes noticeable. Add the indexes now before data grows.

---

## Requirement 3 — Data Fetching & Caching

### Already implemented ✓
- `@tanstack/react-query` v5 installed
- `QueryClientProvider` wrapping the app in `App.tsx`

### Missing ✗ — React Query is set up but **never actually used**
Every page fetches data with raw `useEffect` + `supabase` calls. Zero caching, zero background refetch, no optimistic updates anywhere.

**Boilerplate hook pattern to follow for every data type:**

```ts
// hooks/use-invoices.ts
import { useQuery, useMutation, useQueryClient } from '@tanstack/react-query';
import { supabase } from '@/integrations/supabase/client';

export function useInvoices() {
  return useQuery({
    queryKey: ['invoices'],
    queryFn: async () => {
      const { data, error } = await supabase
        .from('invoices')
        .select('*')
        .order('created_at', { ascending: false });
      if (error) throw error;
      return data;
    },
    staleTime: 1000 * 60 * 2,      // treat as fresh for 2 min — no refetch on tab switch
    gcTime:    1000 * 60 * 10,      // keep in memory 10 min after unmount
  });
}

export function useCreateInvoice() {
  const queryClient = useQueryClient();
  return useMutation({
    mutationFn: async (invoice: any) => {
      const { data, error } = await supabase.from('invoices').insert(invoice).select().single();
      if (error) throw error;
      return data;
    },
    // Optimistic update — UI shows the new invoice instantly before DB confirms
    onMutate: async (newInvoice) => {
      await queryClient.cancelQueries({ queryKey: ['invoices'] });
      const previous = queryClient.getQueryData(['invoices']);
      queryClient.setQueryData(['invoices'], (old: any[]) => [
        { ...newInvoice, id: 'temp-id', created_at: new Date().toISOString() },
        ...(old ?? []),
      ]);
      return { previous };
    },
    onError: (_err, _vars, context) => {
      queryClient.setQueryData(['invoices'], context?.previous);
    },
    onSettled: () => {
      queryClient.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: ['invoices'] });
    },
  });
}
```

**Also add proper `QueryClient` config in `App.tsx`** — the current setup uses defaults which are too aggressive for a SaaS:

```ts
const queryClient = new QueryClient({
  defaultOptions: {
    queries: {
      staleTime: 1000 * 60 * 2,   // 2 min — prevents refetch on every tab focus
      retry: 1,                    // only retry once on failure
      refetchOnWindowFocus: false, // don't refetch just because user switched tabs
    },
  },
});
```

---

## Requirement 4 — Asset & UI Rendering

### Already implemented ✓
- `preconnect` for Google Fonts
- Named Lucide imports (tree-shakeable — only used icons ship)
- No analytics scripts bloating TTI

### Issue 1 — Google Fonts blocks render ✗

Your current setup:
```html
<!-- BLOCKS render until fonts download -->
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?..." rel="stylesheet">
```

Fix — non-blocking font load:
```html
<!-- Non-blocking: loads as print, swaps to all when ready -->
<link rel="preload" as="style"
  href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Vollkorn:wght@400;600;700;800&family=Poppins:wght@300;400;500;600;700&display=swap"
  onload="this.rel='stylesheet'">
<noscript>
  <link rel="stylesheet"
    href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Vollkorn:wght@400;600;700;800&family=Poppins:wght@300;400;500;600;700&display=swap">
</noscript>
```

**Also:** `Dancing Script`, `Great Vibes`, and `Caveat` appear to only be used in invoices/canvas signature fields. Move them to a separate non-blocking link so they don't delay the main app.

### Issue 2 — Paystack script blocks TTI ✗

```html
<!-- CURRENT — synchronous, blocks everything -->
<script src="https://js.paystack.co/v1/inline.js"></script>
```

Fix:
```html
<!-- Deferred — loads after page is interactive -->
<script src="https://js.paystack.co/v1/inline.js" defer></script>
```

### Issue 3 — Images have no size hints (CLS risk) ✗

Every `<img>` without explicit `width` and `height` causes layout shift as it loads. Rule:
```tsx
// Always set width + height OR use aspect-ratio in CSS
<img src={url} width={48} height={48} className="w-12 h-12 rounded-full object-cover" />

// For dynamic/unknown sizes — reserve space with aspect-ratio
<div className="aspect-square w-12">
  <img src={url} className="w-full h-full object-cover rounded-full" />
</div>
```

---

## Summary — What's Done vs. What's Needed

| Item | Status |
|---|---|
| SWC compiler | Done ✓ |
| Route-level code splitting | Done ✓ |
| PWA + Supabase runtime cache | Done ✓ |
| `manualChunks` vendor splitting | **Missing** |
| DB indexes on Kira/notifications | Done ✓ |
| DB indexes on invoices, canvases, chat, profiles | **Missing** |
| React Query installed + wired | Done ✓ |
| React Query actually used for data fetching | **Missing** |
| QueryClient configured with sane defaults | **Missing** |
| Fonts non-blocking | **Missing** |
| Paystack script deferred | **Missing** |
| Lucide tree-shaking | Done ✓ |
| Image CLS prevention | **Missing** |

---

Shall I go ahead and implement all the missing items — `manualChunks`, DB indexes, QueryClient config, font + Paystack fix? The DB indexes and Vite config are zero-risk quick wins. React Query hooks are the biggest effort but highest impact.

